---
import LegalLayout from '../../../layouts/LegalLayout.astro'
import { getAppBySlug, LAST_UPDATED, SUPPORT_EMAIL } from '../../../legal-config'

const app = getAppBySlug('gymmate')
---

<LegalLayout
  title="Privacy Policy"
  appName={app.name}
  lastUpdated={LAST_UPDATED}
  description="How GymMate handles account data, training records, Apple Health data, analytics, AI parsing, notifications, and privacy requests."
>
  <h2>1. Introduction</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy explains how GymMate handles information when you use the app. GymMate is a
    training companion for planning workouts, logging exercise performance, tracking progress,
    managing reminders, and reviewing training history.
  </p>
  <p>
    GymMate is developed and maintained by Nacho Martínez, operating under the Sizle Digital Product
    Studio brand.
  </p>

  <h2>2. Information You Add or Create</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate stores the following information when you choose to add or create it: account email,
    display name, height, body weight entries, target weight, training goals, experience level,
    available training days, training programs, training days, exercises, sets, reps, weights used,
    completed values, workout dates, workout duration, warm-up exercises, notes, achievements,
    onboarding progress, guided tour status, notification preferences, and exported training files.
  </p>
  <p>
    Some of this information may be health or fitness-related because it describes your workouts,
    physical metrics, training habits, and progress. You should avoid adding information that you do
    not want stored or processed by the app.
  </p>

  <h2>3. Information Processed by Optional Features</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate may process the following information only when you enable or use the related feature:
    Sign in with Apple or Google sign-in information, Apple Health and Apple Watch workout data,
    push notification subscriptions, local notification settings, device and browser information,
    product analytics events, crash and error diagnostics, AI program parsing input, offline sync
    queue data, exported files, and share sheet data.
  </p>
  <p>
    If you use Sign in with Apple, Apple may provide GymMate with your name, email address, private
    relay email address, and provider identifier depending on your Apple ID choices. If you use
    Google sign-in, Google may provide account identifiers and profile information needed to sign in.
    This information is used to create or access your GymMate account and provide account-related
    functionality.
  </p>

  <h2>4. Local Storage, Sync, and Backups</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate uses local device storage, including IndexedDB or platform storage, so the app can work
    quickly and support offline-first workflows. Training changes made offline may be queued locally
    and synced with Supabase when connectivity returns.
  </p>
  <p>
    Account-backed training data is stored and synced with Supabase so your account, programs,
    workout logs, body weight entries, achievements, notification settings, push subscriptions, and
    related records can be available across sessions and devices where supported.
  </p>
  <p>
    Exported files may include training programs, exercise details, workout history, body metrics,
    notes, achievements, notification settings, and account-related records. Anyone with access to an
    exported file may be able to view the information contained in it. Keep exported files in a safe
    location and avoid sharing them with people you do not trust.
  </p>

  <h2>5. Apple Health, Apple Watch, and Fitness Data</h2>
  <p>
    If you use Apple Health or Apple Watch features and grant permission, GymMate may read heart rate,
    active energy, workout, and related workout session data during training so it can display and
    synchronize workout information. GymMate may also write workout sessions and active energy data
    to Apple Health when you allow it.
  </p>
  <p>
    Apple Health access is controlled by iOS and watchOS permission settings. You can deny or revoke
    Health access and continue using GymMate, although Apple Health or Apple Watch features may be
    limited.
  </p>

  <h2>6. How We Use Information</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate uses information to create and manage your account, save workout programs, log training
    sessions, calculate progress, show charts and summaries, support offline sync, generate
    achievements, send reminders you enable, export your data, provide support, protect the service,
    and maintain app reliability.
  </p>
  <p>
    GymMate does not use third-party advertising SDKs and does not sell personal information.
    GymMate does not use your data to track you across apps or websites owned by other companies.
  </p>

  <h2>7. Analytics and Error Monitoring</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate may use PostHog for product analytics. In the web/PWA experience, analytics depend on
    consent. On native platforms, consent may be treated as accepted by the app configuration. PostHog
    autocapture is disabled, and analytics events are intended to measure product usage such as
    onboarding, workout logging, navigation, performance, and feature adoption.
  </p>
  <p>
    GymMate may use Sentry for crash and error monitoring when configured. Error reports may include
    technical diagnostics such as app version, environment, device or browser information, route
    context, stack traces, and account identifiers needed to debug reliability issues.
  </p>

  <h2>8. AI Program Parsing</h2>
  <p>
    If you use AI-assisted program parsing, the workout text you submit is sent to a Supabase Edge
    Function and processed using Google Gemini to convert that text into a structured training
    program. GymMate also records limited rate-limit information, such as your user identifier and
    request time, to prevent abuse.
  </p>
  <p>
    Do not submit sensitive information in AI parsing prompts unless you are comfortable with that
    information being processed for this feature.
  </p>

  <h2>9. Notifications</h2>
  <p>
    If you enable notifications, GymMate may store notification preferences, reminder times, weekly
    summary settings, push subscription endpoints, device names, user agents, delivery status, and
    notification logs. You can manage notification permissions in iOS Settings or browser settings
    and notification preferences inside the app where available.
  </p>

  <h2>10. Third-Party Services</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate uses Supabase for authentication, database storage, sync, account deletion, data export,
    Edge Functions, and push-notification-related records. GymMate may use Apple services such as
    Sign in with Apple, Apple Health, Apple Watch, Live Activities, widgets, share sheets, and
    notifications where enabled by the operating system.
  </p>
  <p>
    GymMate may use Google sign-in and Google Gemini for the optional AI parsing feature. GymMate may
    use PostHog for analytics and Sentry for crash/error monitoring as described above.
  </p>

  <h2>11. Purchases and Subscriptions</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate does not receive full payment card details. If paid plans, in-app purchases, or
    subscriptions are offered in the future, the specific features, price, billing period, renewal
    terms, and cancellation information will be shown before purchase. Apple-billed purchases, if
    offered, are processed through Apple&apos;s App Store.
  </p>

  <h2>12. Data Retention</h2>
  <p>
    Local data remains on your device until you delete it, sign out where local cleanup occurs,
    uninstall the app, reset the device, clear browser storage, or otherwise remove the data.
    Account-backed data is retained while your account is active unless deleted through account
    deletion, data management tools, or support requests, subject to verification, backups, security,
    and legal retention requirements.
  </p>

  <h2>13. User Rights and Privacy Requests</h2>
  <p>
    Depending on your location, you may have rights to access, correct, delete, export, restrict, or
    object to certain uses of personal information. GymMate provides account deletion and data export
    functionality where available. You can also contact support for privacy requests using the email
    below.
  </p>

  <h2>14. Security</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate relies on Apple platform security, Supabase security controls, local device protections,
    and provider security controls for account, sync, analytics, error monitoring, and notification
    services. No method of storage or transmission is completely secure, so you should protect your
    device, Apple ID, Google account where used, GymMate account, and any exported files.
  </p>

  <h2>15. Children&apos;s Privacy</h2>
  <p>
    GymMate is not directed to children under the age where parental consent is required by
    applicable law. If you believe a child has provided personal information through GymMate, contact
    us so we can review the request.
  </p>

  <h2>16. Changes to This Policy</h2>
  <p>
    This Privacy Policy may be updated from time to time. The latest version will be posted on this
    page with an updated date.
  </p>

  <h2>17. Contact</h2>
  <p>
    For privacy questions, data requests, export requests, or deletion requests, contact <a
      href={`mailto:${SUPPORT_EMAIL}`}>{SUPPORT_EMAIL}</a
    >.
  </p>
</LegalLayout>
